Every single project—whether it's a console app, a Jetpack Compose app, or a complete Android application—will begin with these six steps:

    Business Problem
    Requirements
    Data Identification
    Business Rules
    Algorithm / Flow
    Implementation

Only after these six steps will we write code.

This is how professional engineers avoid writing code that solves the wrong problem.
It also aligns perfectly with the software architecture mental model you've committed to following,
so every new topic will fit into a consistent way of thinking rather than feeling like isolated Kotlin syntax.

